{
  "message": "fuzz(openfs-recovery): 21 structured seeds across SeedImage \u00d7 mutations \u00d7 options\n\nfuzz_openfs_recovery drives `OpenFs::from_device` against four\nfabricated images (Ext4Clean / Ext4Dirty / BtrfsClean / BtrfsTreeLog),\nwith a mutate_bytes pass that targets EXT4_INTERESTING_OFFSETS or\nBTRFS_INTERESTING_OFFSETS (8 ext4 + 12 btrfs locations covering\nsuperblock magic / state / journal pointers / chunk array / log\nroot). Existing 4 ad-hoc seeds covered only the no-mutation defaults\nfor each SeedImage variant.\n\nAdds 21 seeds covering:\n\n  Clean defaults \u00d7 replay-mode toggles:\n  * Ext4Clean with Apply / Skip; both `skip_validation` settings.\n  * Ext4Dirty with Apply / SimulateOverlay.\n  * BtrfsClean default + skip_validation toggle.\n  * BtrfsTreeLog default + log_root pre-stamp + checksum re-stamp\n    bool combinations.\n\n  Mutation paths against the interesting-offset table:\n  * Ext4 blocks_count (idx 0) \u2192 mutate_byte op\n  * Ext4 state byte (idx 2) \u2192 xor_byte op\n  * Ext4 journal_uuid (idx 3) \u2192 zero_range op\n  * Ext4 inode_size (idx 3) \u2192 write_u16_le zero\n  * Ext4 last_orphan (Dirty, idx 6) \u2192 write_u32_le all-FF\n  * Btrfs csum_type (idx 7) \u2192 write_u16_le bogus\n  * Btrfs log_root (idx 4) \u2192 write_u32_le zero\n  * Btrfs tree_log chunk array \u2192 overwrite_range\n  * Multi-mutation: u32 blocks_count + zero state in one round\n\n  Coverage shapes:\n  * Ext4Dirty with orphan_flag bool=1 setting orphan_head=5\n  * BtrfsTreeLog with both log_root + checksum-stamp bools=1\n  * Ext4Clean with one wide-round overwriting bytes [0x1000..0x1020)\n    (catches the wide-mutation-only path the focused-only seeds miss)\n\nValidated with `-runs=0` over the 21 new seeds in isolation: 22\ninputs loaded, coverage rose to 1 896 PCs / 2 319 features, no\nloader-time crashes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
